comments.value: Occupational asthma (OA) and allergic contact dermatitis (ACD); Occupational asthma has been reported in workers exposed to polyurethanes, phenolic and amino resins, anhydrides, and amine curing agents (N,N-Dimethyl-1,3-propanediamine, ethylenediamine, triethylene tetramine, dimethylethanolamine, isophorone diamine, hexamethylenetetramine). [Malo]
